title: Cincinnati's baseball past hailed as All-Star Week arrives
text:
68°   Seasonal affective disorder Cincinnati's baseball past hailed as All-Star Week arrives 
CINCINNATI — The city hosting baseball’s all-star game this year was the home of a team that played like all-stars back in 1869. That year, the Cincinnati Red Stockings went 57-0 as baseball’s first official all-professional team. Before the season, player-manager Harry Wright’s team added new players, led by his brother, George, who was credited with a .633 batting average and 49 homers.
